Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.60,0:12:28.40,1080P_CN_Up,,0,0,0,,字幕翻译给虫，欢迎点赞投币收藏转发分享评论关注充电~
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.54,0:00:06.68,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,(恰饭时间)本视频由Squarespace赞助，详情前往下方链接
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.54,0:00:06.68,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,This video was made possible by Squarespace. Build your website for 10% at squarespace.com/Wendover
Dialogue: 1,0:00:07.08,0:00:10.76,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,17年前人类打破了一个航空界纪录
Dialogue: 2,0:00:07.08,0:00:10.76,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,17 years ago, an aviation frontier was broken
Dialogue: 1,0:00:10.92,0:00:13.60,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,2001年3月1日中午之前
Dialogue: 2,0:00:10.92,0:00:13.60,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Just before noon on March 1, 2001
Dialogue: 1,0:00:13.60,0:00:19.08,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,一架波音777洲际客机从寒冷的纽约城河对岸纽瓦克机场起飞
Dialogue: 2,0:00:13.60,0:00:19.08,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,a Continental Airlines 777 lifted off from frosty Newark Airport across the river from New York City
Dialogue: 1,0:00:19.20,0:00:25.04,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,一路向北飞过美国、加拿大，过了北极变成了向南飞
Dialogue: 2,0:00:19.20,0:00:25.04,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,It tracked north over the US, then Canada, then just kept flying north until north became south
Dialogue: 1,0:00:25.04,0:00:28.52,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,然后飞过俄罗斯、蒙古、中国大陆
Dialogue: 2,0:00:25.04,0:00:28.52,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,It flew south over Russia, then Mongolia, then mainland China
Dialogue: 1,0:00:28.52,0:00:33.14,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,在16小时的飞行后降落在香港赤鱲角机场
Dialogue: 2,0:00:28.52,0:00:33.14,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,before setting down at Chek Lap Kok Airport in Hong Kong after 16 hours
Dialogue: 1,0:00:33.14,0:00:36.08,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,该航班因此成为世界上最长的航班
Dialogue: 2,0:00:33.14,0:00:36.08,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,With that, there was a new longest flight in the world
Dialogue: 1,0:00:36.08,0:00:40.10,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,两座城市之前从未有过直飞商业航班
Dialogue: 2,0:00:36.08,0:00:40.10,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,The two cities had never before been connected by non-stop commercial flights
Dialogue: 1,0:00:40.18,0:00:43.16,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,这在当时是一个里程碑式的成就
Dialogue: 2,0:00:40.18,0:00:43.16,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,This was at the time a momentous achievement
Dialogue: 1,0:00:43.16,0:00:48.82,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,所有频繁往返这两大经济中心的商务旅客都迫切希望该航班尽早开通
Dialogue: 2,0:00:43.16,0:00:48.82,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,—all the business travelers making frequent trips between the two financial centers badly wanted this quicker flight
Dialogue: 1,0:00:48.82,0:00:52.76,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,但你可能很奇怪这种航班怎么在21世纪才开通
Dialogue: 2,0:00:48.82,0:00:52.76,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,—but you may be surprised that such a flight was an achievement so recently
Dialogue: 1,0:00:52.82,0:00:57.40,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,而如今，纽约直飞香港的航班已经很常见了
Dialogue: 2,0:00:52.82,0:00:57.40,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Nowadays, non-stop New York to Hong Kong flights are far from exceptional
Dialogue: 1,0:00:57.46,0:01:02.44,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,每天有五架飞机载着上千名旅客在两个城市之间直飞
Dialogue: 2,0:00:57.46,0:01:02.44,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Five planes carrying more than 1,000 passengers total fly non-stop daily between the two cities
Dialogue: 1,0:01:02.44,0:01:07.24,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,而且在今天这种航班根本挤不进世界最远程航班前20名
Dialogue: 2,0:01:02.44,0:01:07.24,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,and nowadays, this route doesn’t even crack the list of the top 20 longest flights in the world
Dialogue: 1,0:01:07.42,0:01:13.80,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,尤其是最近三年，这种超远程航班呈现一种急剧增长的趋势
Dialogue: 2,0:01:07.42,0:01:13.80,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Especially in the past three years, there’s been a noticeable and dramatic rise in the number of ultra-long haul flights
Dialogue: 1,0:01:13.96,0:01:19.54,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,接下来列举最长直飞航班前十名，排在第十的是2009年开通的
Dialogue: 2,0:01:13.96,0:01:19.54,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Among the ten longest non-stop flights, the one on this list that’s existed the longest, since 2009
Dialogue: 1,0:01:19.88,0:01:24.12,1080P_CN_Up,,0,0,0,,左上是排名 右上是机型\N左下是距离 中下是起降时间 右下是运营航司
Dialogue: 1,0:01:19.54,0:01:22.24,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1200,0,330,,达美航空每日从约翰内\N斯堡飞亚特兰大的航班
Dialogue: 2,0:01:19.54,0:01:22.24,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1200,0,260,,is Delta’s daily service from Johannesburg to Atlanta
Dialogue: 1,0:01:22.24,0:01:24.98,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1200,0,330,,这是美国的航司\N唯一一个飞南非的航班
Dialogue: 2,0:01:22.24,0:01:24.98,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1200,0,260,,—the only flight by an American airline to South Africa
Dialogue: 1,0:01:24.98,0:01:29.20,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1200,0,330,,在2016年，美联航开始\N从旧金山直飞新加坡
Dialogue: 2,0:01:24.98,0:01:29.20,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1200,0,260,,In 2016 United started non-stop flights between San Francisco and Singapore
Dialogue: 1,0:01:29.20,0:01:32.94,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1200,0,330,,终结了两个国家之间\N没有直飞航班的一段时间
Dialogue: 2,0:01:29.20,0:01:32.94,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1200,0,260,,—ending an era during which there were no non-stop connections between the two countries
Dialogue: 1,0:01:32.94,0:01:39.60,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1000,0,330,,在2018年10月，菲律宾航空开始\N用新买的A350从马尼拉直飞纽约
Dialogue: 2,0:01:32.94,0:01:39.60,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1000,0,260,,Just recently in October, 2018 Philippine Airlines began flying from Manila to New York non-stop on their new A350
Dialogue: 1,0:01:39.72,0:01:44.06,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1150,0,330,,2014年，澳大利亚航空\N推出悉尼直飞达拉斯的航班
Dialogue: 2,0:01:39.72,0:01:44.06,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1200,0,260,,In 2014, Qantas starting flying non-stop in both directions from Sydney to Dallas
Dialogue: 1,0:01:44.12,0:01:45.96,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1200,0,330,,成为在当时\N世界上最远程的航班
Dialogue: 2,0:01:44.12,0:01:45.96,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1200,0,295,,—then the longest flight in the world
Dialogue: 1,0:01:46.08,0:01:51.46,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1150,0,330,,在2018年年初美联航增加了\N休斯顿直飞悉尼的航班
Dialogue: 2,0:01:46.08,0:01:51.46,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1080,0,260,,In early 2018 United added another connection to down under with their route from Houston to Sydney
Dialogue: 1,0:01:51.56,0:01:56.36,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1030,0,330,,新加坡航空在2018年11月\N添加另一个飞美国洛杉矶的航班
Dialogue: 2,0:01:51.56,0:01:56.36,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1200,0,260,,Singapore Airlines added another US connection in November 2018 flying to Los Angeles
Dialogue: 1,0:01:56.44,0:02:02.26,1080P_CN_Bottom,,800,0,330,,阿联酋航空从2016年开始执飞\NA380机型的最远航线——迪拜到奥克兰
Dialogue: 2,0:01:56.44,0:02:02.26,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1000,0,260,,and Emirates has operated the longest nonstop A380 flight in the world from Dubai to Auckland since 2016
Dialogue: 1,0:02:02.32,0:02:07.76,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1150,0,330,,澳航在2018年3月开启\N首个澳洲到欧洲的直飞航班
Dialogue: 2,0:02:02.32,0:02:07.76,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1100,0,260,,Qantas started the first and currently only non-stop connection between Australia and Europe in March, 2018
Dialogue: 1,0:02:07.76,0:02:10.10,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1400,0,330,,执飞机型为787-9，\N从珀斯飞到伦敦
Dialogue: 2,0:02:07.76,0:02:10.10,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1400,0,260,,with their daily dreamliner service from Perth to London
Dialogue: 1,0:02:10.10,0:02:15.22,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1050,0,330,,卡塔尔航空有到前不久为止\N最长的航班——多哈到奥克兰
Dialogue: 2,0:02:10.10,0:02:15.22,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1100,0,260,,and Qatar operates what was until recently the longest non-stop flight from Doha all the way to Auckland
Dialogue: 1,0:02:15.30,0:02:20.10,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1200,0,330,,而全世界航程最远的航班，\N超过了第二名五百英里
Dialogue: 2,0:02:15.30,0:02:20.10,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1100,0,260,,Lastly, the longest flight in the world, confidently beating the runner up by over 500 miles
Dialogue: 1,0:02:20.16,0:02:23.92,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1000,0,330,,是新加坡航空的每天从\N新加坡飞纽约纽瓦克机场的航班
Dialogue: 2,0:02:20.16,0:02:23.92,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1200,0,260,,is the newly launched daily Singapore Airlines flight between Singapore and Newark
Dialogue: 1,0:02:23.92,0:02:30.24,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1100,0,330,,距离9534英里(15343公里)，\N飞行时间因风而定最多19小时
Dialogue: 2,0:02:23.92,0:02:30.24,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1200,0,260,,clocking in at 9,534 miles and up to 19 hours of flight time depending on winds
Dialogue: 1,0:02:30.24,0:02:33.96,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,这十个航班里有八个是最近三年开通的
Dialogue: 2,0:02:30.24,0:02:33.96,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Eight of the ten flights on this list were launched in the past three years
Dialogue: 1,0:02:33.96,0:02:38.04,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,虽然可以理解为随着科技发展飞机能飞的更远了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:33.96,0:02:38.04,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,While it can be expected that as technology advances airplane range will get longer
Dialogue: 1,0:02:38.04,0:02:43.56,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,但这种地球上远距离城市之间直飞航班的增长趋势是很明显的
Dialogue: 2,0:02:38.04,0:02:43.56,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,there’s been a noticeable acceleration in the addition of non-stop routes between earth’s furthest city pairs
Dialogue: 1,0:02:43.64,0:02:46.74,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,就像各种现象一样，有成因也有影响
Dialogue: 2,0:02:43.64,0:02:46.74,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Like any phenomenon, this has causes and effects
Dialogue: 1,0:02:46.74,0:02:49.42,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,驱使超远程航班出现的一个原因
Dialogue: 2,0:02:46.74,0:02:49.42,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,One factor driving this surge in ultra-long haul flights
Dialogue: 1,0:02:49.42,0:02:54.16,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,是过去十年内两款新飞机的诞生——A350和787
Dialogue: 2,0:02:49.42,0:02:54.16,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,is the release of two new planes in the past decade—the A350 and 787
Dialogue: 1,0:02:54.16,0:02:57.54,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,上述十个航班有六个由这两种飞机执飞
Dialogue: 2,0:02:54.16,0:02:57.54,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Six of the ten longest routes are flown by one of these two planes
Dialogue: 1,0:02:57.54,0:03:02.72,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,之前也出现过能飞这种距离的飞机，但它们经济性太差
Dialogue: 2,0:02:57.54,0:03:02.72,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Now, planes have existed before that could fly the routes these fly but they weren’t as economical
Dialogue: 1,0:03:02.84,0:03:06.18,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,新加坡航空在2004年到2014年曾经使用A340
Dialogue: 2,0:03:02.84,0:03:06.18,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Singapore Airlines previously flew the world’s longest flight from Singapore to Newark from 2004 until 2014 on the A340
Dialogue: 1,0:03:06.18,0:03:09.34,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,执飞新加坡到纽瓦克航班，是当时世界上距离最远的航班
Dialogue: 2,0:03:06.18,0:03:09.34,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Singapore Airlines previously flew the world’s longest flight from Singapore to Newark from 2004 until 2014 on the A340
Dialogue: 1,0:03:09.34,0:03:13.74,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,但A340的高油耗让他们在油价上涨的时候不得不取消这条线路
Dialogue: 2,0:03:09.34,0:03:13.74,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,but its high fuel consumption forced them to cancel the route as soon as oil prices ticked up
Dialogue: 1,0:03:14.08,0:03:20.66,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,A340运力不如A350，航程不如A350，油耗却比A350高35%
Dialogue: 2,0:03:14.08,0:03:20.66,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,To fly fewer passengers a shorter maximum distance, an A340 uses 35% more fuel than the A350
Dialogue: 1,0:03:20.84,0:03:24.08,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,对于这些世界级超远程航班，经济效益就是一切
Dialogue: 2,0:03:20.84,0:03:24.08,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Economics is everything with the world’s longest routes
Dialogue: 1,0:03:24.24,0:03:28.78,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,因为从新加坡直飞纽约的航班燃油消耗要比
Dialogue: 2,0:03:24.24,0:03:28.78,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,The truth is that flying a non-stop flight from Singapore to New York uses more fuel
Dialogue: 1,0:03:28.78,0:03:32.26,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,新加坡飞东京再飞纽约的经停航班多
Dialogue: 2,0:03:28.78,0:03:32.26,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,than flying a stopping service from Singapore to Tokyo to New York
Dialogue: 1,0:03:32.40,0:03:38.06,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,这听上去可能有点反直觉，因为飞机起降时耗油比巡航时多得多
Dialogue: 2,0:03:32.40,0:03:38.06,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Now, this might seem counterintuitive since planes use far more fuel per minute taking off than they do in cruise
Dialogue: 1,0:03:38.06,0:03:41.04,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,而直飞航班只要一次起飞，而不是两次
Dialogue: 2,0:03:38.06,0:03:41.04,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,and flying nonstop requires one take off instead of two
Dialogue: 1,0:03:41.04,0:03:44.54,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,但你们忘了，携带大量燃料飞行需要消耗额外的燃料
Dialogue: 2,0:03:41.04,0:03:44.54,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,but that's failing to consider that it uses fuel to carry fuel
Dialogue: 1,0:03:44.54,0:03:50.80,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1000,0,330,,以777-200为例，飞行800海里\N的航班，平均每英里耗油30.6磅
Dialogue: 2,0:03:44.54,0:03:50.80,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1000,0,260,,With a 777-200, for example, flying 800 nautical miles will use about 30.6 pounds of fuel per mile
Dialogue: 1,0:03:50.80,0:03:57.06,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1000,0,330,,“平均每英里油耗(磅)”数值在航程\N增加到3000海里中不断下降
Dialogue: 2,0:03:50.80,0:03:57.06,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1000,0,260,,That pounds per mile average decreases up until reaching a total flight distance of about 3,000 nautical miles
Dialogue: 1,0:03:57.12,0:04:01.92,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1000,0,330,,而超过3000海里后，该数值又\N会增加，直到航程上限8000海里
Dialogue: 2,0:03:57.12,0:04:01.92,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1000,0,260,,Beyond that, the pound per mile figure increases up until 8,000 nautical miles
Dialogue: 1,0:04:01.92,0:04:05.74,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1200,0,330,,在8000海里时，飞机\N平均每英里油耗32.2磅
Dialogue: 2,0:04:01.92,0:04:05.74,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1300,0,260,,where the aircraft would burn 32.2 pounds of fuel per mile flown
Dialogue: 1,0:04:05.84,0:04:10.88,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,这是因为到了最后，携带大量燃料远程飞行所需的额外燃料
Dialogue: 2,0:04:05.84,0:04:10.88,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,This is because eventually, the added burn from flying the extra fuel needed to fly long distance
Dialogue: 1,0:04:10.88,0:04:13.58,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,已经超过了起飞所需的额外燃料了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:10.88,0:04:13.58,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,overtakes the extra fuel used to take off
Dialogue: 1,0:04:13.72,0:04:15.62,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,这意味着使用这种飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:04:13.72,0:04:15.62,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,That means that, with this aircraft
Dialogue: 1,0:04:15.62,0:04:19.92,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,本来卡塔尔航空用它从多哈直飞休斯顿的8000英里
Dialogue: 2,0:04:15.62,0:04:19.92,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,which is used to fly the daily 8,000 mile Qatar flight between Doha and Houston
Dialogue: 1,0:04:19.92,0:04:24.36,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,却不如经停飞行更加节省燃料，比如从多哈先飞巴黎
Dialogue: 2,0:04:19.92,0:04:24.36,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,it would be more efficient on a fuel consumption basis to fly something like Doha to Paris
Dialogue: 1,0:04:24.36,0:04:28.74,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,然后巴黎飞哈利法克斯，再从哈利法克斯飞休斯顿
Dialogue: 2,0:04:24.36,0:04:28.74,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Paris to Halifax, and Halifax to Houston rather than flying the whole trip in one go
Dialogue: 1,0:04:28.86,0:04:33.08,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,这也是货运航空极少飞超远程航线的原因之一
Dialogue: 2,0:04:28.86,0:04:33.08,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,This is part of the reason why cargo airlines rarely fly ultra-long haul routes
Dialogue: 1,0:04:33.18,0:04:38.14,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,尽管UPS有足够多的的货物去支持路易斯维尔到香港的直飞航线
Dialogue: 2,0:04:33.18,0:04:38.14,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,While UPS has plenty enough cargo to support a non-stop flight between their Louisville and Hong Kong hubs
Dialogue: 1,0:04:38.16,0:04:43.90,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,机型也能做到直飞，他们还是会经停安克雷奇，部分原因就是省油
Dialogue: 2,0:04:38.16,0:04:43.90,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,and the aircraft that could fly it in one go, they fly the route with a stop in Anchorage partially for fuel saving reasons
Dialogue: 1,0:04:43.98,0:04:48.50,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,当然，飞机停留多了会影响飞机多拉快跑多赚钱
Dialogue: 2,0:04:43.98,0:04:48.50,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Of course, any time on the ground is time that an aircraft could be in the air making money
Dialogue: 1,0:04:48.52,0:04:54.16,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,这对节省下油钱的削弱也是货航不会只飞3000英里就经停的部分原因
Dialogue: 2,0:04:48.52,0:04:54.16,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,so that degrades the savings and that’s part of why cargo airlines don’t only fly in 3,000 mile hops
Dialogue: 1,0:04:54.28,0:04:58.66,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,时间对货航固然重要，但对民航更加重要
Dialogue: 2,0:04:54.28,0:04:58.66,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Time matters for cargo airlines but not nearly as much as it does for passenger airlines
Dialogue: 1,0:04:58.78,0:05:00.66,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,民航拉的是人
Dialogue: 2,0:04:58.78,0:05:00.66,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Passenger airlines have to deal with people
Dialogue: 1,0:05:00.66,0:05:04.52,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,人比快递对多出来的几个小时旅行时间更加敏感
Dialogue: 2,0:05:00.66,0:05:04.52,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,which are far more sensitive to a few extra hours of travel time than boxes
Dialogue: 1,0:05:04.60,0:05:08.32,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,直飞航班尤其对于商务旅客来讲需求很高
Dialogue: 2,0:05:04.60,0:05:08.32,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Non-stop flights are typically more desirable especially to the business traveller
Dialogue: 1,0:05:08.32,0:05:12.46,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,这也是为什么航司会把过站航班定价高于直飞航班
Dialogue: 2,0:05:08.32,0:05:12.46,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,which is why airlines will price connecting itineraries typically higher than non-stop ones
Dialogue: 1,0:05:12.46,0:05:18.56,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,无论多短的航线，航司运营过站航班的成本也要比直飞航班高
Dialogue: 2,0:05:12.46,0:05:18.56,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,even on short routes where the cost to the airline of operating a connecting itinerary is higher than that of a non-stop flight
Dialogue: 1,0:05:18.56,0:05:24.04,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,因为过站的成本高，航司才会开始考虑运营直飞航班而不是过站航班
Dialogue: 2,0:05:18.56,0:05:24.04,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,With higher costs, airlines therefore need to justify operating non-stop flights instead of stopping ones
Dialogue: 1,0:05:24.18,0:05:29.16,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,新加坡航空还用更大的A380执飞新加坡过站法兰克福到纽约的航班
Dialogue: 2,0:05:24.18,0:05:29.16,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Singapore airlines does operate another flight to New York via Frankfurt with a far larger A380
Dialogue: 1,0:05:29.16,0:05:33.70,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,但直飞航班主要还是面对能付更多钱的商务旅客
Dialogue: 2,0:05:29.16,0:05:33.70,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,but the non-stop flight is primarily operated to appeal to the business traveller who can pay more
Dialogue: 1,0:05:33.92,0:05:38.70,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,一般能够运营超远程航班的两个城市都有很多的商务往来
Dialogue: 2,0:05:33.92,0:05:38.70,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Often, the routes with enough demand to support ultra long-haul flights are the ones with high business traffic
Dialogue: 1,0:05:38.70,0:05:42.70,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,比如悉尼、新加坡、香港、纽约这样比较富有的大城市
Dialogue: 2,0:05:38.70,0:05:42.70,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,between big, wealthy cities like Sydney, Singapore, Hong Kong, London, and New York
Dialogue: 1,0:05:42.86,0:05:47.04,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,即使是世界著名旅游胜地夏威夷
Dialogue: 2,0:05:42.86,0:05:47.04,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Even though Hawaii, for example, is one of the top vacation destinations in the world
Dialogue: 1,0:05:47.12,0:05:50.30,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,你也找不到几个从那直飞伦敦的远程航班
Dialogue: 2,0:05:47.12,0:05:50.30,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,you just don’t see many long-haul flights to it from places like London
Dialogue: 1,0:05:50.30,0:05:52.82,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,因为去旅游的人对价格很敏感
Dialogue: 2,0:05:50.30,0:05:52.82,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,because leisure travelers are more sensitive to price
Dialogue: 1,0:05:52.82,0:05:57.30,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,他们愿意花更少钱在洛杉矶转机而不是花更多钱从伦敦直飞
Dialogue: 2,0:05:52.82,0:05:57.30,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,and they’d rather pay less to fly via Los Angeles rather than on a non-stop from London for more
Dialogue: 1,0:05:57.50,0:06:01.22,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,也因此，新加坡航空用于飞纽瓦克机场的A350上
Dialogue: 2,0:05:57.50,0:06:01.22,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,For this reason, on the A350’s Singapore Airlines uses to fly to Newark
Dialogue: 1,0:06:01.22,0:06:05.47,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,根本没有那种旅游的乘客经常会订的经济舱座位
Dialogue: 2,0:06:01.22,0:06:05.47,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,they didn’t even bother including an economy class, the kind that leisure travelers tend to book
Dialogue: 1,0:06:05.47,0:06:08.18,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,而是只有高级经济舱和商务舱
Dialogue: 2,0:06:05.47,0:06:08.18,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,They only have premium economy and business class
Dialogue: 1,0:06:08.30,0:06:11.00,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,更少的座位、更少的乘客、更少的行李，就是更少的重量
Dialogue: 2,0:06:08.30,0:06:11.00,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,With the lower weight from fewer bags, seats, and passengers
Dialogue: 1,0:06:11.00,0:06:13.66,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,飞机可以更加高效地飞往地球另一边
Dialogue: 2,0:06:11.00,0:06:13.66,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,the plane can fly more efficiently to the other side of the world
Dialogue: 1,0:06:13.66,0:06:16.82,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,并且从航司角度来看，他们也没损失太多
Dialogue: 2,0:06:13.66,0:06:16.82,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,and, from the airlines perspective, they’re not loosing out on much
Dialogue: 1,0:06:16.82,0:06:22.48,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,毕竟要是卖经济舱的话票价就要低得有竞争力，更赚不到多少钱
Dialogue: 2,0:06:16.82,0:06:22.48,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,since, at the prices they would have to sell economy seats at to be competitive, they really wouldn’t be making much money anyways
Dialogue: 1,0:06:22.58,0:06:26.96,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,高级舱位的高利润让他们即使在这种超远程航班中也能赚到不少钱
Dialogue: 2,0:06:22.58,0:06:26.96,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,The higher margins of premium classes give them a better shot of breaking even on this flight
Dialogue: 1,0:06:26.96,0:06:32.08,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,当然，超远程航班爆发的另一个因素是油价的降低
Dialogue: 2,0:06:26.96,0:06:32.08,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Of course, the other factor contributing to the rise of these ultra-long haul flights is the low cost of fuel
Dialogue: 1,0:06:32.18,0:06:39.52,1080P_CN_Bottom,,900,0,800,,航空燃油的价格在2015年减半，\N并在2016年1月以每加仑85美分触底
Dialogue: 2,0:06:32.18,0:06:39.52,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1100,0,730,,Jet fuel prices halved in 2015 and bottomed out at a cost of only 85 cents per gallon in January 2016
Dialogue: 1,0:06:39.52,0:06:44.50,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1000,0,800,,之后油价又温和增长，导致人们\N开始质疑航空业是否进入了寒冬
Dialogue: 2,0:06:39.52,0:06:44.50,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1000,0,730,,Since then prices have steadily risen leading some to question whether troubled times were ahead for the industry
Dialogue: 1,0:06:44.50,0:06:47.54,1080P_CN_Bottom,,1200,0,800,,但2018年10月油价又跌了
Dialogue: 2,0:06:44.50,0:06:47.54,1080P_EN_Bottom,,1200,0,765,,but prices again took a dive in October 2018
Dialogue: 1,0:06:47.54,0:06:51.00,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,反正总的来说，过去四年，油价的确比以前便宜不少
Dialogue: 2,0:06:47.54,0:06:51.00,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Overall, over the past four years, prices are lower than ever
Dialogue: 1,0:06:51.00,0:06:57.26,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,而油价降低带来航司成本降低，使得远程航班成本有所降低
Dialogue: 2,0:06:51.00,0:06:57.26,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,and with that fuel represents a smaller proportion of an airline’s cost so it’s proportionally cheaper to fly longer distances
Dialogue: 1,0:06:57.26,0:07:00.60,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,这种油价的波动带来了一些航司的崛起
Dialogue: 2,0:06:57.26,0:07:00.60,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,This fluctuation in fuel cost has also contributed to the rise
Dialogue: 1,0:07:00.60,0:07:06.16,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,也导致一些类似Norwegian、Wow和Primra等长途廉价航空的衰落
Dialogue: 2,0:07:00.60,0:07:06.16,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,and in some cases fall, of long haul budget airlines such as Norwegian Airlines, Wow Air, and Primera Air
Dialogue: 1,0:07:06.16,0:07:10.20,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,所以我们理清了超远程航班雨后春笋般涌现的原因
Dialogue: 2,0:07:06.16,0:07:10.20,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,So we’ve established the causes of this proliferation of ultra-long flights
Dialogue: 1,0:07:10.20,0:07:12.00,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,但它的影响是什么？
Dialogue: 2,0:07:10.20,0:07:12.00,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,but what are its effects?
Dialogue: 1,0:07:12.12,0:07:17.48,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,往返澳洲、新西兰与欧洲的航线是最繁忙的远程航线之一
Dialogue: 2,0:07:12.12,0:07:17.48,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,One of the busiest long distance flows of passengers is from Europe to Australia and New Zealand and vice versa
Dialogue: 1,0:07:17.60,0:07:20.38,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,两地的文化类似，又有频繁的商业往来
Dialogue: 2,0:07:17.60,0:07:20.38,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,As two areas with close cultural and business connections
Dialogue: 1,0:07:20.38,0:07:24.96,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,尽管单程要花24小时，但还是有很多人往返两地
Dialogue: 2,0:07:20.38,0:07:24.96,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,plenty of people travel between them despite it taking about 24 hours each way
Dialogue: 1,0:07:24.96,0:07:30.32,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,在上世纪几乎每个飞往澳洲的欧洲大航司都会中途经停某处
Dialogue: 2,0:07:24.96,0:07:30.32,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Before the turn of the century almost every major European Airline flew to Australia via some stopping point
Dialogue: 1,0:07:30.32,0:07:36.18,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,如法航、荷航、汉莎、意大利航、英航会经停曼谷、新加坡或者香港
Dialogue: 2,0:07:30.32,0:07:36.18,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,like Bangkok, Singapore, or Hong Kong including Air France, KLM, Lufthansa, Alitalia, and British Airways
Dialogue: 1,0:07:36.18,0:07:38.22,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,有些每天还有多个航班
Dialogue: 2,0:07:36.18,0:07:38.22,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,—some with multiple daily flights
Dialogue: 1,0:07:38.33,0:07:42.56,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,而今天，只有一个欧洲航司的一个航班飞往澳洲
Dialogue: 2,0:07:38.33,0:07:42.56,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Today, though, there is only one sole flight by a European Airlines to Australia
Dialogue: 1,0:07:42.56,0:07:45.86,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,那就是英航，每天一班伦敦飞悉尼，过站新加坡
Dialogue: 2,0:07:42.56,0:07:45.86,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,—British Airways’ once daily flight from London to Singapore to Sydney
Dialogue: 1,0:07:46.00,0:07:50.40,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,同时，澳航、纽航也是各自国家唯一一个有飞往欧洲航班的航司
Dialogue: 2,0:07:46.00,0:07:50.40,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, Qantas is the only Australian Airline and Air New Zealand the only Kiwi airline
Dialogue: 1,0:07:50.40,0:07:52.46,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,同时，澳航、纽航也是各自国家唯一一个有飞往欧洲航班的航司
Dialogue: 2,0:07:50.40,0:07:52.46,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,to operate services all the way to Europe
Dialogue: 1,0:07:52.54,0:07:57.36,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,两边的航司们都损失了中间亚洲航空公司的市场份额
Dialogue: 2,0:07:52.54,0:07:57.36,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,All the airlines on each end have lost market share to those in between—the Asian airlines
Dialogue: 1,0:07:57.46,0:08:00.34,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,过去几十年像阿联酋和新加坡航这样的航司
Dialogue: 2,0:07:57.46,0:08:00.34,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,In the past few decades airlines like Emirates and Singapore Airlines
Dialogue: 1,0:08:00.34,0:08:03.82,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,成为了人们在两地之间旅行最受欢迎的选择
Dialogue: 2,0:08:00.34,0:08:03.82,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,have become the most popular for those traveling between the two areas as
Dialogue: 1,0:08:03.82,0:08:07.40,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,因为如果你要是坐英航，那你就必须从悉尼起飞，最终只能到达伦敦
Dialogue: 2,0:08:03.82,0:08:07.40,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,if you were to fly British Airways you would have to start in Sydney and end in London
Dialogue: 1,0:08:07.54,0:08:13.34,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,但如果选阿航，你可以从澳洲或新西兰里六个直飞迪拜的城市出发
Dialogue: 2,0:08:07.54,0:08:13.34,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Flying on Emirates, on the other hand, you can start at any of their six non-stop destinations in Australia and New Zealand
Dialogue: 1,0:08:13.34,0:08:18.92,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,到了迪拜只转机一次，就能飞往欧洲数十个城市了
Dialogue: 2,0:08:13.34,0:08:18.92,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,connect via Dubai, and end up at any of their dozens of European destinations with one stop
Dialogue: 1,0:08:19.02,0:08:24.54,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,这样更快，也通常更便宜，因此英航每周只有7班飞澳洲
Dialogue: 2,0:08:19.02,0:08:24.54,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,It’s just faster and often cheaper and so, while British Airways operates seven weekly flights to Australia
Dialogue: 1,0:08:24.54,0:08:28.58,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,而阿航有84班，新加坡航有137班
Dialogue: 2,0:08:24.54,0:08:28.58,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Emirates operates 84 and Singapore 137
Dialogue: 1,0:08:28.70,0:08:32.57,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,不止阿航和新航，还有国泰、阿提哈德、卡塔尔航空
Dialogue: 2,0:08:28.70,0:08:32.57,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Both of these airlines and more including Cathay Pacific, Etihad, and Qatar Airways
Dialogue: 1,0:08:32.57,0:08:36.08,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,也都成为了运营欧洲飞澳洲航班的能手
Dialogue: 2,0:08:32.57,0:08:36.08,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,have become experts in operating connecting flights between Europe and Australasia
Dialogue: 1,0:08:36.24,0:08:40.14,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,但他们能做到此事的原因是这段旅途你无论如何都要转机或过站
Dialogue: 2,0:08:36.24,0:08:40.14,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,But the reason they’re able to do this is because you have to stop on these routes anyways
Dialogue: 1,0:08:40.14,0:08:43.70,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,因为这个距离太远了，无法直飞，至少以前是这样
Dialogue: 2,0:08:40.14,0:08:43.70,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,—it’s too far for non-stop flights, or rather, it used to be
Dialogue: 1,0:08:43.82,0:08:50.02,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,2018年3月起，开头说的第三名，澳航开通了珀斯飞伦敦的直飞航班
Dialogue: 2,0:08:43.82,0:08:50.02,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Since March, 2018, number three on that list of longest flights is Qantas’ new non-stop flight from Perth to London
Dialogue: 1,0:08:50.12,0:08:54.18,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,很多人怀疑会不会仍然有很多旅客青睐转机一次的选择
Dialogue: 2,0:08:50.12,0:08:54.18,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Many were skeptical when this flight launched that customers would prefer it to a one-stop option
Dialogue: 1,0:08:54.18,0:08:58.50,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,那样更便宜、还能半路歇歇伸伸腿，但最终数据显示恰恰相反
Dialogue: 2,0:08:54.18,0:08:58.50,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,where they could pay less and stretch their legs halfway through their trip but the data proves otherwise
Dialogue: 1,0:08:58.56,0:09:02.44,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,自从该航班开通，其上座位卖出了92%
Dialogue: 2,0:08:58.56,0:09:02.44,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Since launch, 92% of available seats on this route have been sold
Dialogue: 1,0:09:02.56,0:09:05.60,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,这是一个相当不错的客座率
Dialogue: 2,0:09:02.56,0:09:05.60,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,This is an exceptionally good load factor, as its called
Dialogue: 1,0:09:05.60,0:09:09.94,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,因为澳航国际航班的平均客座率只有84%
Dialogue: 2,0:09:05.60,0:09:09.94,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,as Qantas’ average load factor for international flights is only 84%
Dialogue: 1,0:09:10.02,0:09:15.84,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,{\fs64}澳航也因此开始考虑继续开通其他珀斯直飞巴黎、法兰克福的欧洲航班
Dialogue: 2,0:09:10.02,0:09:15.84,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,For this reason Qantas is strongly considering launching other non-stop European routes from Perth to Paris and Frankfurt
Dialogue: 1,0:09:15.96,0:09:20.54,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,而其它航司也着手准备开通新的欧洲飞澳洲的直飞航班
Dialogue: 2,0:09:15.96,0:09:20.54,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,In addition, other airlines are looking at starting new non-stop routes from Europe to Australia
Dialogue: 1,0:09:20.66,0:09:22.20,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,维珍大西洋航空创始人理查德·布兰森说过
Dialogue: 2,0:09:20.66,0:09:22.20,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Founder Richard Branson has said that
Dialogue: 1,0:09:22.20,0:09:26.42,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,维珍大西洋航空正着手准备“尽快”开通伦敦到珀斯的直飞航班
Dialogue: 2,0:09:22.20,0:09:26.42,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Virgin Atlantic is looking to start non-stop flights from London to Perth, “as soon as possible.”
Dialogue: 1,0:09:26.64,0:09:30.42,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,位于伊斯坦布尔的土耳其航空，是一个欧洲的航司
Dialogue: 2,0:09:26.64,0:09:30.42,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Turkish Airlines, based in Istanbul, is technically still a European Airline
Dialogue: 1,0:09:30.42,0:09:32.42,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,虽然就离亚欧的边界几英里
Dialogue: 2,0:09:30.42,0:09:32.42,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,even if it’s just miles from the border with Asia
Dialogue: 1,0:09:32.42,0:09:36.26,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,而该航空将成为了第一个欧洲直飞悉尼的航空公司
Dialogue: 2,0:09:32.42,0:09:36.26,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,and it’s set to become to first airline to start flying non-stop from Europe to Sydney
Dialogue: 1,0:09:36.26,0:09:41.80,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,前提是其按照公布的计划，在2019年使用新买的787执飞此航班
Dialogue: 2,0:09:36.26,0:09:41.80,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,if it follows through with its announced plans to launch these flights in 2019 with its new 787 dreamliners
Dialogue: 1,0:09:41.96,0:09:46.62,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,澳航每日一班就已经对亚洲的那些航司利润有影响了
Dialogue: 2,0:09:41.96,0:09:46.62,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,While the once daily Qantas flight is doing little to cut into the Asian carrier’s profits right now
Dialogue: 1,0:09:46.68,0:09:49.50,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,如果越来越多的航班不经停亚洲的中转机场
Dialogue: 2,0:09:46.68,0:09:49.50,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,if more and more flights start bypassing the Asian hubs
Dialogue: 1,0:09:49.50,0:09:52.39,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,那原本连接澳洲与欧洲的亚洲航空公司就会损失一大部分利润
Dialogue: 2,0:09:49.50,0:09:52.39,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,the major connecting airlines could be given a run for their money
Dialogue: 1,0:09:52.39,0:09:57.14,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,与此同时，一场比赛也悄然打响，谁能最先开通可能是最有价值的
Dialogue: 2,0:09:52.39,0:09:57.14,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, the race is on to see who will start flying what is perhaps the most valuable route in the world
Dialogue: 1,0:09:57.14,0:10:00.56,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,之前从未有过直飞的线路，比如悉尼到伦敦
Dialogue: 2,0:09:57.14,0:10:00.56,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,that doesn’t yet have a non-stop connection—Sydney to London
Dialogue: 1,0:10:00.68,0:10:02.90,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,澳航将首先得到这个机会
Dialogue: 2,0:10:00.68,0:10:02.90,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Chances are the first will be Qantas
Dialogue: 1,0:10:03.04,0:10:06.66,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,多年以前，澳航就向飞机制造商波音、空客提出需求
Dialogue: 2,0:10:03.04,0:10:06.66,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,A number of years ago, Qantas challenged aircraft manufacturers Boeing and Airbus
Dialogue: 1,0:10:06.66,0:10:11.42,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,让他们造出能从悉尼满载出发、不间断飞行21小时直飞伦敦的飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:10:06.66,0:10:11.42,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,to create a plane that could fly the 21 hour non-stop flight fully loaded all the way to London
Dialogue: 1,0:10:11.54,0:10:15.38,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,制造商那边很快就要交付了，而澳航说他们要在
Dialogue: 2,0:10:11.54,0:10:15.38,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,The manufacturers are close to delivering and Qantas has said they will make their decision
Dialogue: 1,0:10:15.38,0:10:21.02,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,空客A350-1000ULR与波音777-8之间做出选择，2019年底给答复
Dialogue: 2,0:10:15.38,0:10:21.02,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,between the Airbus A350-1000ULR or Boeing 777-8 by the end of 2019
Dialogue: 1,0:10:21.12,0:10:25.72,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,航班可能会在2022年或2023年开通，到时候就不止是悉尼飞伦敦了
Dialogue: 2,0:10:21.12,0:10:25.72,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,From there, flights would start in 2022 or 2023 not only on the Sydney to London route
Dialogue: 1,0:10:25.72,0:10:29.42,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,还可能是墨尔本或者布里斯班飞纽约或巴黎
Dialogue: 2,0:10:25.72,0:10:29.42,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,but also potentially from Melbourne and Brisbane and to New York and Paris
Dialogue: 1,0:10:29.54,0:10:31.62,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,作为澳大利亚人的首选航空公司
Dialogue: 2,0:10:29.54,0:10:31.62,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Being the airline of choice for Australians
Dialogue: 1,0:10:31.62,0:10:37.58,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,恐怕全世界没有谁能像澳航那样驾驭21小时直飞的超远程航班了
Dialogue: 2,0:10:31.62,0:10:37.58,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,perhaps no airline globally has a better shot at making a 21 hour non-stop flight work than Qantas
Dialogue: 1,0:10:37.70,0:10:43.42,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,随着最新机型的交付，飞机可以连续飞行11000英里(17000公里)
Dialogue: 2,0:10:37.70,0:10:43.42,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,With the arrival of the newest set of planes, airlines can now fly as far as 11,000 miles non-stop
Dialogue: 1,0:10:43.54,0:10:48.92,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,这意味着地球上几乎任意两个大人口城市都能直飞
Dialogue: 2,0:10:43.54,0:10:48.92,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,That means that nearly every populated point on earth can feasibly be connected by non-stop flights
Dialogue: 1,0:10:49.10,0:10:54.72,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,随着科技的不断进步，估计不久地球上任意两点都能做到直飞了
Dialogue: 2,0:10:49.10,0:10:54.72,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,With more technological advancements on their way, absolutely every point on earth will soon be reachable non-stop
Dialogue: 1,0:10:54.92,0:10:59.16,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,这说明，限制超远程航班发展的唯一阻碍
Dialogue: 2,0:10:54.92,0:10:59.16,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,What that means is that the only factors now restricting the development of ultra-long haul flights
Dialogue: 1,0:10:59.16,0:11:01.34,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,是经济性，而不是技术难度
Dialogue: 2,0:10:59.16,0:11:01.34,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,are economic, not technological
Dialogue: 1,0:11:01.46,0:11:05.81,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,在许多方面，关于超远程航班的增长趋势问题的答案
Dialogue: 2,0:11:01.46,0:11:05.81,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,In many ways, the question of whether this trend of the proliferation of ultra-long haul flight
Dialogue: 1,0:11:05.81,0:11:07.70,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,都和燃油价格有关
Dialogue: 2,0:11:05.81,0:11:07.70,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,is up to the mercy of fuel prices
Dialogue: 1,0:11:07.70,0:11:11.90,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,如果油价持续走低，那就会有越来越多的18、19甚至20小时的航班
Dialogue: 2,0:11:07.70,0:11:11.90,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,If they stay low, we’ll have more and more 18, 19, or 20 hour flights
Dialogue: 1,0:11:11.90,0:11:15.70,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,但如果涨了，你放心吧航司肯定会取消这些航班的
Dialogue: 2,0:11:11.90,0:11:15.70,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,while if they go up, you can be sure that airlines will cancel these routes in droves
Dialogue: 1,0:11:15.80,0:11:20.54,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,飞机虽然速度没有变快，但利用直飞缩短了旅途时间
Dialogue: 2,0:11:15.80,0:11:20.54,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,While the planes are not flying any faster, they’re getting passengers to their destination in less time
Dialogue: 1,0:11:20.58,0:11:23.14,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,所以这些新的直飞到地球另一边的航班
Dialogue: 2,0:11:20.58,0:11:23.14,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,so these new non-stop routes to the other side of the world
Dialogue: 1,0:11:23.14,0:11:26.96,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,正在帮助拉近彼此的距离，让世界越来越小
Dialogue: 2,0:11:23.14,0:11:26.96,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,are helping to make the world just a little bit smaller, one flight at a time
Dialogue: 1,0:11:27.60,0:11:32.70,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,以下仍然是恰饭时间
Dialogue: 2,0:11:27.60,0:11:32.70,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,If you have an idea for a business, whether it be just you as a freelancer or the next Fortune 500 company
